President Cyril Ramaphosa answers questions in the NCOP * Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa is taking questions from the National Council of Provinces. He is joining its sitting virtually. Issues he's being quizzed on include gender-based violence, COVID-19 tender corruption, the use of a military plane for an ANC trip to Zimbabwe, and, of course, the economy.